p:
Two polioviruses (isolated by L20B cell) and one non-polio enterovirus (isolated by RD cell) were isolated from AFP patients and nine polioviruses (isolated by L20B cell) and 90 non-polio enteroviruses (isolated by RD cell) were isolated from health children. The Online Enterovirus Genotyping Tool identifies the VP1 region of each strain to show that six non-polio enteroviruses ( 99245, 99258, 99267, 99268, 99269, and 99275) belong to EV-B83
16 . BLAST was used for sequence alignment, which showed that the VP1 region of the six strains and the EV-B83 prototype strain ( CA76-10392/USA/1976) exhibited 80% similarity in the GenBank.
